On January 28, the Beijing News reported from the Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University that Guo Qin, a nurse in the Emergency Department of the hospital, had been infected after treating a patient with severe pneumonia in COVID-19 for several days. After recovering on January 27, she volunteered to return to work.

That night, busy for more than 10 hours Guo Qin told reporters, was also afraid of being diagnosed, but she believed in his colleagues and medical team. After arriving at the post, she shared her experience with the patient, hoping to tell others that the new coronavirus can be cured. "Don't panic, we work together, everything will be fine. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan University south-central Hospital nurse Guo Qin due to work inadvertently infected with a new type of pneumonia, cured after the initiative to return to work. Photo by Gao Xiang, correspondent

━━━━━

Leave a suicide note for your family before isolation if you are infected during treatment

Beijing News: How is your health now?

Guo Qin: my nucleic acid test was negative on January 25, and again on January 27. The result is still negative. Since the end of the isolation period, my physical condition is normal.

Beijing News: How did you get infected?

Guo Qin: I am a nurse in the emergency department. After the outbreak of the disease, many fever patients went to the hospital. I take care of the serious patients in the emergency ward every day. Nearly 100 patients are admitted and cared for every day. I stayed in the ward for ten hours.

I later learned that I had been infected by droplets or contact during my treatment of COVID-19.

Beijing News: How is your health after the infection?

Guo Qin: January 12 at 22 pm, I have a fever, body temperature 37.8 degrees, that night I took fever medicine. The second day, I began to have a headache, high fever, limb fatigue, joints and muscle pain, call the hospital for emergency, ambulance pulled me away from home. After being diagnosed with COVID-19 pneumonia, the hospital put me in an isolation ward.

Beijing News: Are you afraid after the diagnosis?

Guo Qin: Just a fever was pulled away by the ambulance, I am more worried and frustrated, mouth advised family not to worry, let my husband at home do not come to see me, but still left a "last words" to her husband.

"If I die, I will take care of my 11-year-old son and the old people on both sides. "

And then I thought, what kind of patient hasn't been exposed to in years. After graduating from college, I worked as a nurse in the central South Hospital for 15 years. I have been working in the emergency department's Intensive Care Unit. So many patients with severe diseases have been saved. I have to trust my colleagues and my team to successfully deal with the epidemic.

My colleagues gave me hugs and encouragements and, to be honest, my inner worries and frustrations soon passed.

Beijing News: At that time medical staff did what protection?

Guo Qin: we usually wear blue isolation suits and medical masks. This year, we wear N95 masks, goggles, blue isolation suits on the inside and a white protective suit on the outside.

Spring and winter are the seasons of high incidence of influenza. Around New Year's Day this year, fever has come to our hospital for treatment. The number of patients and patients infected with influenza is particularly high, at least twice as many as in previous years. Some of them have been diagnosed as, cOVID-19 pneumonia.

We have to deal with a lot of people every day, and even with good protection, there's no guarantee that we won't be infected.

Our home is more than 40 minutes away from the hospital, those days busy up to five hours of sleep every day. Sleep is insufficient, meal can not eat on time, immunity also drops somewhat.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Before this, the new type of pneumonia patient Mr. Hu received treatment in Wuhan University Zhongnan Hospital. Photo by Gao Xiang, correspondent

To get a bed for home quarantine

Beijing News: How is infection treated?

Guo Qin: In the hospital isolation that day, I take and infusion of anti-virus, anti-bacterial drugs, the next day fever, the body is much more relaxed.

There were new infections every day, and there weren't enough hospital beds, so I asked to go home and be quarantined.

For a few days at home, I was taking Duffy, an anti-flu drug. Another is meat and eggs, add protein, eat fresh fruits and vegetables, so that the body to maintain a relaxed state.

Beijing News: Will Isolation Treatment at Home Affect family members?

Guo Qin: I live in my mother's house, I live in a room, I have been wearing a mask, in addition to mom and dad to send food, usually do not open the door, occasionally open the window to air. On the day I was taken to the hospital, my family was tested for nucleic acid and there was no infection.

Beijing News: How is the period of isolation treatment spent?

Guo Qin: Before the work is too busy too tired, isolation just a few days to rest, think about the next work plan. There are colleagues and leaders to send me flowers, send books, at home to read medical books, add some prevention and treatment of influenza knowledge, lived quite substantial.

Beijing News: Why Return to work after recovery?

Guo Qin: On my first night in the hospital, it should have been me and another colleague on the night shift, because there were so many patients, and the monitors outside kept ringing, which meant that there were always patients looking for medical help, and I couldn't help, listen to the footsteps of colleagues running around busy, it is very painful.

We had 48 emts in the E.R. , 10 emts in critical care, all three shifts during that time, plus overtime, and they were exhausted.

The second day of Hospitalization, I had a fever, originally want to continue to work, the unit said no, but also continue treatment, isolation observation.

After my recovery, I was in good health. As a nurse and a party member, I wanted to go back to work and share the pressure with my colleagues.

On January 28, the specialist assessed my physical condition was good, I returned to the unit to continue to treat the patient.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"not to be a hero or a deserter. "

Beijing News: Does Your Family Support Your Decision?

Guo Qin: they advised me not to continue to work, said very tactfully. Many relatives in the family group advised me to take a few more days off, said I have a young and old, think about it.

Beijing News: How did you respond to them?

Guo Qin: My husband is a teacher, very supportive of my decision, the children this year in the sixth grade, let me refuel.

I said in the family group that there was a lot of information coming in every day, that the head nurse had been working 48 hours straight, and that the nurses were sick. Being a doctor and a nurse is definitely a risk, but I'll take care of it.

I didn't go back to work to be a hero, but I can't be a deserter.

There was no one left to say anything. Everyone understood.

Beijing News: What changes do you feel after returning to the hospital?

Guo Qin: The hospital sees a patient to reduce apparently, gratified is to return to duty the first day to know, the colleague two weeks ago treats a COVID-19 pneumonia patient also recovered to discharge from the hospital.

The patient, who was initially diagnosed with COVID-19 pneumonia, continued to have a high fever and was in a coma at a very rapid rate. He was successfully treated with ECMO.

But ECMO can only be used in the most severe cases, not in the general population.

Note: According to Public Information, ECMO technique is based on the principle of drawing the venous blood from the body out of the body, then injecting it into the patient's artery or vein system after special material and artificial heart-lung bypass oxygenation, and playing the role of partial heart-lung replacement.

Beijing News: Is the hospital's material reserve sufficient now?

Guo Qin: At first mask, protective clothing and other medical supplies reserve enough, is still enough, but still more nervous.

Masks take four hours to change, drinking water, toilet protective clothing exposed, you need to change. We have nurses in order to save protective clothing, basic do not drink water do not eat, do not go to the toilet, this is not good for their own health.

Beijing News: As an infected person and a nurse, what do you want to say?

Guo Qin: you must believe the doctor, if you don't feel well, you should see a doctor immediately. Now the National Health Commission has issued a diagnosis and treatment plan for pneumonia caused by COVID-19 infection (trial version 4) . The introduction of this disease is very detailed, and the prevention and treatment are also very detailed, you can take a look.

To pay attention to is, do not go to crowded places, go out must wear a mask, mask do not repeat, use. It's not that bad. It's treatable. There's no need to panic.

HSINKING newspaper reporter, Liu Mingyang editor, Li Ming on duty editor, Wang Hongchun, Pan Jiakun proofread Guo Li
